# OOP Refactor Plan

## Classes
### Paddle
- Feature: x, y, width, height, speed
- By using draw(ctx), moveUp(), moveDown(), reset()

### Ball
- Feature: x, y, radius, speedX, speedY, color
- B using draw(ctx), move(), reset(), wallBounce(), paddleBounce(paddle)

### Game
- Feature: canvas, ctx, paddles, ball, scores, gameOver, winningScore
- By using update(), draw(), handleInput(keys), reset(), loop()

- Each class handles its own state and behavior.
- Game coordinates the objects but doesnâ€™t handle their internals.

- Use localStorage to store SpeedBoost toggle and multiplier.
- Game loads/saves these settings.
